                                                            Practical 5 - Install Samba to share folder or files between Windows and Linux.



1 - Install the samba package
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install samba

2 - Create a directory for it to share
mkdir /home/kali/sambashare/
Created two files to test
 
3 - The configuration file. Have to add the directory we want to share.
sudo nano /etc/samba/smb.conf

4 - Add this to the end of the file.
[sambashare]
    comment = Samba on Ubuntu
    path = /home/username/sambashare
    read only = no
    browsable = yes
 
5 - Start/Restart the service
sudo service smbd restart

6 - Allow samba through the firewall
sudo ufw allow samba
 
7 - Setting up User Account
sudo smbpasswd -a kali
 
8 - Open the file explorer, type smb://<ip-address>/<shared_file>
smd://127.0.0.1/sambashare
